The county spent Sh16.15 million on committee sitting allowances for the 44 MCAs and the speaker, against the annual allocation of Sh50.67 million.
Travel expenses
Controller of Budget Margaret Nyakan’go also stated in the report that the assembly spent Sh47.23 million on domestic travel and Sh224,000 on foreign travel.
During the period, the amount of money spent on domestic travel amounted to Sh64.72 million - Sh47.23 million spent by the assembly and Sh17.48 million by the executive.
The foreign travel expense was Sh224,000, which was spent by the assembly, the report states.
In Laikipia, the MCAs were paid Sh112,043, up from the Sh82,923 paid in the first three months of the 2019/2020 financial year.



